    "ideation": "The ideograph 申 (shēn) traditionally signifies 'to explain,' 'to report,' or 'to extend,' and is often associated with the Monkey in the Chinese zodiac. To capture this, the animation moves from a state of compressed, structured thought (representing the boxy frame) into a dynamic, expressive 'reporting' state. The eyes begin as narrow vertical slits to mimic the central vertical stroke of the character, then expand as if gaining a revelation. The mouth acts as the 'extension'—starting as a tight, gritted line of preparation before flowing into a wide, rolling wave that represents the act of speaking or explaining. The color palette uses imperial gold and scholar's crimson to evoke tradition and formal communication.",
